</table>
<p>"Peppermint Pig" is the name of a song by <a href="/wiki/Scotland" title="Scotland">Scottish</a> <a href="/wiki/Alternative_rock" title="Alternative rock">alternative rock</a> band <a href="/wiki/Cocteau_Twins" title="Cocteau Twins">Cocteau Twins</a>. It was released as both a single and EP on 4 April 1983 by record label <a href="/wiki/4AD" title="4AD">4AD</a>. Musically, the material is similar to the previous release, the 1982 EP <i><a href="/wiki/Lullabies" title="Lullabies">Lullabies</a></i>. It was the last release to feature original bass guitar player <a href="/wiki/Will_Heggie" title="Will Heggie">Will Heggie</a>.</p>
<p></p>
